techmeme.title: Match Group reports Q4 revenue down 1% YoY to $860M, forecasts Q1 revenue below est., names Zillow co-founder Spencer Rascoff as CEO; MTCH drops 7%+ after hours (Natalie Lung/Bloomberg)
Robotics startup Figure is exiting its Feb. 2024 OpenAI deal, which aimed to develop AI models for robots, to focus on in-house AI after a "major breakthrough" (Brian Heater/TechCrunch)
Sources: Meta is merging the teams behind Facebook and Messenger into one unit and shuffling its generative AI group, as it prepares for layoffs next week (The Information)
Alphabet expects to invest about $75B in capex in 2025, vs. $59.73B est.; GOOG drops 7%+ after hours after its Q4 revenue missed estimates (Samantha Subin/CNBC)
AMD reports Q4 revenue up 24% YoY to $7.66B, Data Center revenue up 69% to $3.86B, vs. $4.09B est., and forecasts Q1 sales of $6.8B to $7.4B, vs. $7.04B est. (Ian King/Bloomberg)
